  "text": "With regards to improving the propagation modeling using location-specific information, Wang et al. [CITATION_1] utilize aerial photography to determine the density of scatterers in the simulated area. By processing the aerial data to infer the scatterer density, the authors determine the fading level for a given location on the road.",
